# Editing Conventions

## Use Direct Text Editing, Not Scripts

Always use the StrReplace tool (or other built-in IDE editing tools) to modify files. Never write Python scripts, shell one-liners, or `sed`/`awk` commands to batch-edit file contents, even when fixing many similar occurrences.

If there are multiple instances to fix, make multiple StrReplace calls. This keeps changes visible, reviewable, and reversible in the IDE.

## No Em Dashes

Never use em dashes (`—`, Unicode U+2014) in any file. Use a double dash (`--`) instead. Em dashes look AI-generated and are inconsistent with the plain-text style of this repository.

- Bad: `detection and remediation — from webhook configuration`
- Good: `detection and remediation -- from webhook configuration`
